Check out my Twitter where I post daily and you can check my commission status there.

items.name: Rachel Bilson
items.description:
Rachel Bilson is an American actress known for her role as Summer Roberts in the TV series The O.C. and as Zoe Hart in the TV series Hart of Dixie.

This LoRA was trained on SD 1.5, but I was using A Zovya Photoreal V2 to generate renders. This model was created using publicly available images.

I have found the LoRA weight works in the 1.0-1.1 range, I tried not to overtrain it so that it captures the subject but is still flexible to the prompt.

items.name: Evelyn - Hentai University
items.description:
This is a LoRA for the character Evelyn, from Hentai University a game by Noodle Jacuzzi.

Evelyn's art is from the artist Enoshima Iki, the set -

Yokkyuu Fuman no Kanjuku Onnakyoushi ni Yatto Kita Haru

I've been working my way through making these for all the characters currently in the game, and sharing them in the Discord for HU, but figured I should also put them up here.

In general, I'm working from pretty limited image sets, so expect the results to be a bit wonky at times.

I recommend a weight of around 0.5, possibly lower depending if you're combining the character LoRA with other styles/costumes/etc. along with tagging some defining characteristics of the character you're generating. Higher than that can really push the artist's original style, and may cause you issues.

All characters I train have a "character tag" added into the set to help generate them fairly reliably.

Recommended LoRA Weight - 0.5 for fairly flexible, higher if you want more of the original artist's style, lower if it doesn't play nice with other loras.

Character tag - HUEvelyn
Recommended tags - brown eyes, purple hair, ponytail, short hair, large breasts,

Add glasses if you want.

I may have forgotten to check and tag eye color when doing my testing, but hey. If you want it to be "set accurate" be sure to tag.

I've got quite a backlog of these made up already, so I'll be uploading them on and off.

Check my other uploads as I put them out for more HU characters, and if you want any specific character put up soon, let me know.

items.name: Rimjob / Anilingus upside-down
items.description:
LoRA trained to rimjob / anilingus sex act, where the character getting rimmed is kind of upside-down. Most of the dataset includes a female rimming a male, so that is going easier to generate than anything else.

Please rate and leave a like if you enjoyed it! And be sure to follow to check out the upcoming models.

Trigger: rimjob, 1girl, 1boy, penis, testicles, licking

You can make use of the negative prompt to help with the gender of the characters.

This lora works best with square aspect ratio (512x512), then with landscape (768x512) and lastly (occasionally) with portrait (512x768), due to the dataset used.

Although the name of this lora could lead you to the tag upside-down, you should not use this tag in most cases, except perhaps in portrait aspect ratios (e.g. 512x768). See the gallery for examples.

I was planning to include more poses in a single lora but decided to separate it to make it more effective. But if I find a good way to combine multiple poses in a single lora while maintaining flexibility and consistency, I'll post it.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content!

I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

items.name: RealPantyhose: sheer pantyhose
items.description:
Please read the entire post for instructions on how to use the lora

The model is trained using a new dedicated dataset, focusing on sheer pantyhose (tan color or black). The first aim was to improve the appearance of transparent tights for the Realistic Vision model, where legwears have often an opaque appearance (see picture above), and most of the times with artifacts (random horizontal dark bands etc.).

This Lora, based on SD 1.5, is optimized for Realistic Vision (checked also with 3.0) but also gives good results with other models, by changing the weight of the model or the weight of the trigger word.

Trigger word:

RealPantyhose

for tan pantyhose use: tan color RealPantyhose

for black pantyhose use: black color RealPantyhose

Sampling steps recommended: 25-40

¬†

CFG Scale: 7

CHECKPOINTS TESTED

Model and trigger word weight

REALISTIC VISION V2.0, V3.0 and V4.0 (new!!!!):

weight model suggested: 1

trigger word weight: 1 for tan color, 1-1.2 for black color.

¬†

REV_ANIMATED:

weight model suggested: 1.1-1.3

trigger word weight: 0.8-0.9

¬†

XXMix_9realistic:

weight model suggested: 0.9-1

trigger word weight: 1

DELIBERATE_V2:

weight model suggested: 1 for tan color, 1.2 for black color.

trigger word weight: 1.2

DREAMSHAPER_V6.31:

weight model suggested: 1.

trigger word weight: 1 for tan color, 1.2 for black color (sometime may be more effective the use of expression ((black color:1.2) RealPantyhose:1.0) ).

CHILLOUTMIX:

weight model suggested: 1.

trigger word weight: 1 for tan color, 1.2 for black color (sometime may be more effective the use of expression ((black color:1.2) RealPantyhose:1.0) ).

¬†

If prompt is very long and structured, inpainting is suggested to obtain a more effective result.

Effectiveness on more checkpoints will be tested.

On Realistic vision this Lora is compatible with Opentoe heels/sandals with legwears. The use of Opentoe lora is reccomended with inpainting algorithm.

¬†

Possible future release may include white sheer pantyhose color.

Feedbacks well accepted.

This is a mixed pot. Originally, I wanted to create an exploration about the clothing of 55 ethnic minorities in China. Unfortunately, the training didn't yield perfect results as it failed to accurately represent the distinct characteristics of each individual ethnic group's traditional attire. items.name: Nerura „Å≠„Çã„Çâ | Akiba Meido Sensou
items.description:
Nerura from Akiba Meido Sensou (Akiba Maid War)


Update v1b (3rd August 2023):

  • Retrained the model with a bit more anime art style.
    (At first, I wanted to quickly retrain the model with the anime style. However, I realized that training characters with only a single outfit could make the model too inflexible, especially if I aim to retain higher outfit accuracy. Therefore, I decided to experiment with regularization images and also use the OUTALL blocks for further training.)

  • Manually removed image backgrounds from the dataset instead of trying to do so with differential training.

  • Experimented with Prodigy.

    P.S. The badge on her dress and the legwear are still not accurate.
    P.S.2 My 13-year-old hard disk is dead. I won't regather the datasets of the old models and retrain them unless there are real reasons to do so.
    P.S.3 Due to RL reasons, such as the need to get a fking job, I will have less time to have fun with model training.


Prompts (v1b):-

  • Trigger Words:

nerura_olis, blue hair, single braid, side braid, hair bow, pink eyes

  • Outfit:

blue headwear, detached collar, neck ribbon, frilled dress, wrist cuffs, asymmetrical legwear

  • Extra:

1girl, solo
(please refer to my sample images)

Weight: 1 (you may experiment yourself)

Anime Style Model (v1):
I trained a anime style model for experimentation. It is a LoRA-C3Lier/Locon, but it seems to work properly without an extension? (tested on AUTOMATIC1111 WebUI v1.3.2) You can use both the character model and style model together to replicate her in anime style.

All my models were trained with 512x512 pixels.
For optimal results, please upscale your generated outputs with your preferred methods.

My tenth model.

I continued my experimentation with differential training. This time, I attempted to reduce the influence of the image backgrounds of the dataset by doing differential training with a style model trained specifically on those backgrounds. The results were positive, I guess. Besides, I once again did some simple block weight extraction, and trained an anime style model, aiming to minimize the anime style of the character model with differential training, followed by finetuning...blah blah blah

So, I have complicated my workflow again, and I don't think this is worth the time and effort. Many others can train better models without all these complexities.

Anyway, I found this process enjoyable. Hopefully some of you will like the models.

items.name: Diives- Style LoRA
items.description:
INTRODUCTION

800 Images used for training check Diives out https://www.patreon.com/diives

In short, this LoRA does it's best to replicate Diive's style, if you don't know who he is (which...if you're even remotely on the internet how can you not? Especially in this avenue of the net) look him up. You'll probably be there for a while because his discography is pretty sizable. Recommendations will be below. If I were to describe it, his style is semi retro mixed with a stylistic flare only he has, but not anymore MWAHAHAHAHA...I hope. This is my first LoRA creation so this probably just sucks without me realizing, but that's what the comment section is for, go ahead and degrade me all you want as long as there's at least some information I can use to try and potentially make this LoRA better. Made using https://github.com/hollowstrawberry/kohya-colab


BEFORE

This LoRA can be nsfw or not, I'd attest to nsfw due to the fact many of the free Diive videos are censored so the ai may struggle in coming up with...how should I put this...genitalia structure, work with boobies just fine most of the time.

The whole furry thing has been a mystery to me, I'm not sure how to get the ai to identify furry prompts consistently even through a few hours of testing. The closest I've gotten is the ears and tails.

Feel free to experiment and tell what has worked for you in the comments, this is my first LoRA so I can only get better. I know all of you are sweaty nerds anyway.

The ai will sometime fight when it comes to positions though this again is an inconsistency, for example if you tell a character to stand in the prompt the output will probably not have the character standing

It has potential to work with other LoRAs yes, I haven't tested it with any game characters however.

Please don't be a bitch and use this LoRA like a menace to society, credit to Dave for his amazing work. With that being said do not distribute this model or refuse to credit Me and Diives, actually just Diives he's the one that did all the work with all the artwork. Anyway let's get into the recommendations.

Recommendations (I would prefer you do some experimenting, this is just a starting place)

  • Sampling Method: DPM++SDMKerras But I recommend you experiment, see what works. Be sure to help out and tell what you found worked in the comments, I'm just ball parking it as of late.

  • Sampling Steps 30

  • Hiresfix on, steps: 15

  • I have to use 512/512 because if I don't my 8gb of ram prehistoric laptop will explode, I'd think using the anime upscale will work fine but prove me wrong.

  • Denoising Strength: 0.7

  • CFG scale: 9

  • ADetailer(1): face_yolov8n ADetailer(2): hand_yolov8n

  • Inpainting: Restore faces after ADetailer

  • For the weight I recommend starting with 0.7, you'll know when the weights should be moved when the generated image is a bit too bright and or distorted. Shouldn't be moved past 0.5~0.8 from I can see

    Keep in mind that this LoRA was tested with this model it may not work with others, it was also trained with the same checkpoint.

    check Diives out https://www.patreon.com/diives
    That's it from me, peace!

items.name: Cloth Bulge
items.description:
This LoRA is intended to simulate more realistic bulges when characters are wearing skirts and dresses. It generally performs better with skirts, but can still generate dressed based bulges, but may require more finetuning and more generations. It can do various poses but prefers standing or sitting poses as this was the majority of images used to train this LoRA.

The basic prompt is skirt and cloth bulge, but you can use dress as well. Various types of skirts and dresses such as pleated or pencil also work, though results may vary. Using erection under clothing does sometimes help, but you may need to add penis to the negative if you start seeing unwelcome penises appearing. This model can generate male characters as well, though expect them to appear more feminine due to nature of dataset and prompt.

items.name: Two unique Loose socks 2ÂÄã„É´„Éº„Ç∫„ÇΩ„ÉÉ„ÇØ„Çπ„Å™Áèç„Åó„ÅÑ
items.description:
This is my first LoRA.

Two unique Loose socks. (aka boot socks, slouch socks, hooter girl socks, baggy socks etc.)

Both trained with 26 images.

Mainly for 3D but can be used for 2D as well but prone to collapse.

Kinda difficult to use. Due to lack of experience, some poses tend to be fixed or broken.

Only in 2D, sock tends to absorb skin tone/sock color wants to be black.(idk why!)

Would like to improve it, though it's too complicated for me at now and won't happen anytime soon.

1.) BaggySocksLayer

Loose socks worn over knee-highs. Seen in the past 20 years or so in Japan.

Recommended range:

3D, 0.8-1.3

2D, 1.1-1.5

Yet knee-highs struggle to appear.

2.) BaggySocksPlain

Loose socks without elastic band(in contrast of the "Ribbed ones").

This type was seen in the mid-1990s. Extincted fast. Very rare nowadays. Often seen in manga and anime. (cause they are easy to draw?) Most known with Mikoto Misaka and her sisters of "A Certain Scientific Railgun" and Uncho Kanu from "Ikki Tousen / Battle Vixens".

Recommended range:

3D, 0.9-1.1

2D, 0.8-1.4

Btw, the TRUE "Gomu-nuki Loose socks" has almost no wrinkles compared to this LoRA. Sadly, said images are hard to come by these days.

x.)BaggySocksSuper

Been called "Super Loose socks" because of its excessive length.

Some being over 180cm(6ft) before worn, in most case taller than the wearer.

You can easily tell by its ridiculous amounts of wrinkles that covers the entire calf.

Definitely not a cheap sock.

*The outcome is not what I expected, but I'll put it up anyway.

Refrain from commercial purposes.

Thanks to Civitai and its energetic folks.

items.name: Miyuki - Azur Lane - LoRA by artkoikoi
items.description:
Miyuki - Azur Lane - LoRA by artkoikoi

Consider supporting me on Patreon for more models and content.
This was requested by a patron.

Trained using DAdaptAdam optimizer in Kohya. Following most of this settings.
DIM: 32 / Alpha 4
Precision bf16

Checkpoint: NAI

Image quantity: 17

Max Resolution 576,576

Current epoch: 180
Total epochs: 500
Recommended weight (depends on the checkpoint): 0.6-1.0.

Please give me feedback on the weight and I might upload a different epoch for this. I've tested and mostly the best one was at 180 as it gets less confused with tail x clothes. Sometimes it produces more bells, so try using (bell:0.9) to reduce the strength a little bit on that.

Required Trigger Word

miyuki_\\(azur lane)\\

Recommended tags:

positive: multicolored hair, animal ears, tail, bell, yellow eyes
negative: multiple tails

I recommend using Textual Inversions to have better results with image, I'm only using FastNegativeV2 for this post to maintain less influence as possible.

Please credit me when using any of my models.
Specially when merging this model.
You cannot use my models in other generation websites without my permission.
